To Send an OTP from Python to PHP, you can use the 'requests' library in Python, and in PHP, you can use the 'file_get_contents' function. Below is an example:

Python (Using requests library):

import requests

url = "https://cpaas.messagecentral.com/verification/v2/verification/send?country=IN&customerId=C-X9DFA4D3F7BXXX&flowType=SMS&mobileNumber=9XXXXXX25"

payload = {}

headers = {

'authToken': '<authToken>',

'Content-Type': 'application/json'

}

response = requests.request("POST", url, headers=headers, data=payload)

print(response.text)


PHP:

<?php

$url = "https://cpaas.messagecentral.com/verification/v2/verification/send?country=IN&customerId=C-X9DFA4D3F7BXXX&flowType=SMS&mobileNumber=9XXXXXX25";

$options = array(

'http' => array(

'method' => "POST",

'header' => "authToken: <authToken>\r\n" .

"Content-Type: application/json\r\n",

'content' => $data

)

);

$context = stream_context_create($options);

$result = file_get_contents($url, false, $context);

echo $result;

?>

In both the Python and PHP code, make sure to replace '<authToken>' with the actual authentication token received from the token generation API. 

